CUCULUS, SIVE szrs ET HIEMIs CONFLICTUS.

A hexameter poem, a sort of eclogue-—unlike any of Bede’s other works. Opp. i. 35-37. It may be genuine. But in Dummler, Poetae Lat. Aeui Caroling. i. 270, it is printed among Alcuin’s works; and this is probably right ².

PAssro SANCTI Iesum MARTYRIS.

A hexameter poem. Certainly spurious. Opp. i. 38—49.

MARTYROLOGIUM POETICUM.

A hexameter poem. Certainly spurious. It mentions the death of Wilfrid II, who died in 744 or 745. Ib. 50-53. Werner, however, accepts it as genuine, treating the verses on Wilfrid as an interpolation (pp. 102, 146).
